<div id="math-case-study-quiz">
  <section>
    <h2>Case Study 2: Relations and Functions</h2>
    <p>
      In a class of 12th-grade students, the teacher wants to examine the friendship patterns among the students to understand social dynamics. Let the set of boys in the class be <strong>B = {b₁, b₂, b₃}</strong> and the set of girls be <strong>G = {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</strong>. A relation <strong>F</strong> is defined from <strong>B</strong> to <strong>G</strong>, where <em>(bᵢ, gⱼ)</em> means boy <em>bᵢ</em> considers girl <em>gⱼ</em> as a friend. The relation is given by the set <strong>{(b₁, g₁), (b₁, g₂), (b₂, g₂), (b₂, g₃), (b₃, g₄)}</strong>. Based on this, answer the following multiple-choice questions:
    </p>
  </section>

  <form id="quiz-form">
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>What is the domain of the relation F?</p>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"> (a) {b₁, b₂, b₃}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> (b) {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> (c) {b₁, b₂}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="d"> (d) {b₁, b₂, b₃, g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label>
        <p class="solution" style="display:none;"><strong>Answer:</strong> (a) {b₁, b₂, b₃} — Domain is the set of all first elements (boys).</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>What is the range of the relation F?</p>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> (a) {b₁, b₂, b₃}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> (b) {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> (c) {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="d"> (d) {b₁, g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label>
        <p class="solution" style="display:none;"><strong>Answer:</strong> (c) {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄} — Range includes all second elements in the relation.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>Determine the codomain of the relation F.</p>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a"> (a) {b₁, b₂, b₃}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> (b) {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> (c) {g₁, g₂, g₃}</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="d"> (d) {b₁, b₂, b₃, g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄}</label>
        <p class="solution" style="display:none;"><strong>Answer:</strong> (b) {g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄} — Codomain is the set G (all girls).</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>How many elements does the relation F have?</p>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="a"> (a) 4</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="b"> (b) 5</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="c"> (c) 6</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="d"> (d) 3</label>
        <p class="solution" style="display:none;"><strong>Answer:</strong> (b) 5 — There are 5 ordered pairs in the relation.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>Is the relation F a function from B to G?</p>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="a"> (a) Yes</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="b"> (b) No</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="c"> (c) Cannot be determined</label><br>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="d"> (d) Only if B has more elements</label>
        <p class="solution" style="display:none;"><strong>Answer:</strong> (b) No — A function assigns only one value to each element in the domain. Here, b₁ maps to two girls.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <button type="button" onclick="submitQuiz()">Submit</button>

    <div id="quiz-result" style="display:none; margin-top:1em;">
      <p><strong>Correct Answers:</strong> <span id="correct-count"></span></p>
      <p><strong>Incorrect Answers:</strong> <span id="incorrect-count"></span></p>
      <p><strong>Score:</strong> <span id="score-percent"></span>%</p>
    </div>
  </form>

  <style>
    #math-case-study-quiz {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: auto;
      padding: 10px;
    }
    #math-case-study-quiz h2 {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      color: #2a4b7c;
    }
    #math-case-study-quiz ol {
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    #math-case-study-quiz label {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }
    #math-case-study-quiz .solution {
      background-color: #f0f8ff;
      border-left: 4px solid #4caf50;
      padding: 8px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }
    #math-case-study-quiz button {
      background-color: #2a4b7c;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      cursor: pointer;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
    #math-case-study-quiz button:hover {
      background-color: #1e365c;
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    function submitQuiz() {
      const answers = {
        q1: "a",
        q2: "c",
        q3: "b",
        q4: "b",
        q5: "b"
      };

      let correct = 0;
      for (let q in answers) {
        const selected = document.querySelector('input[name="' + q + '"]:checked');
        if (selected && selected.value === answers[q]) {
          correct++;
        }
      }

      const total = Object.keys(answers).length;
      const incorrect = total - correct;
      const score = (correct * 2 / (total * 2)) * 100;

      document.getElementById("correct-count").innerText = correct;
      document.getElementById("incorrect-count").innerText = incorrect;
      document.getElementById("score-percent").innerText = score.toFixed(2);

      // Show all solutions
      const solutions = document.querySelectorAll("#math-case-study-quiz .solution");
      solutions.forEach(function (el) {
        el.style.display = "block";
      });

      document.getElementById("quiz-result").style.display = "block";
    }
  </script>
</div>
